{"word":"ἀποπαύω","slug":"ἀποπαύω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀποπαύω</b></el> <p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to stop</i> or <i>hinder from, make to cease from</i> a thing, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <el>πολέμου</el> <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>; <el>πένθεος</el> <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>: <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a> <i>to hinder</i> from doing, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>:—<a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a> and <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to leave off</i> or <i>cease from</i>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>; <el>ἐκ καμάτων</el> <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>: <a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a> <i>to leave off</i>, <b><a href='S:Theognis'>Theogn.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> only, <i>to stop, check</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}